      "writtenOn": "2021-02-22T13:45:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see how that\u0027s much of a problem. Those extra calls to maybeReload() should only block briefly (i.e. not until the connection is fixed.\n\n This function locks the mutex, starts fixing in a go routine, and then unlocks the mutex and returns. Those slightly late calls to maybeReload will then lock the mutex, and unlock it after seeing h.client is nil.\n\nAm I missing something?",
